org.joty.common

Class CaselessStringKeyMap<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,T>
        • org.joty.common.CaselessStringKeyMap<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the value instances stored and mapped to the keys.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,T>

    public class CaselessStringKeyMap<T>
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,T>
    An HashMap descendant that offers simple way of use.

    It is for dealing with set of objects of some type <T> mapped on key String-s by being unaware of case of the keys.

    the class provides a bit of assistance for key collisions: the m_overwritable member can be set to true in order to have values overwritten on collision.
